Working Principle

When a user places their finger on the sensor, the system captures and processes the fingerprint image. The fingerprint is then matched against stored templates inside the AS608 sensor.

If a valid match is found:

User information is retrieved.
Current date and time are obtained from the RTC.
Attendance information is generated.
The record is saved in LittleFS memory.
The record is simultaneously saved on the SD card.
A background task uploads the record to the cloud when internet connectivity is available.

This workflow ensures uninterrupted attendance operation even in offline environments.

